o usyhoo unlike its larger rival goog  isn’t seeing any revenue boost yet from its investments productdevelopment costs surged  in the third quarter compared with the same period a year ago while revenue slipped  on a yearoveryear basis minus trafficacquisition costs or tac that helps explain why yahoo’s thirdquarter operating income showed a yearoveryear drop of  after that important metric had climbed  during the first six months of  yahoo reported its thirdquarter results late tuesday much of that higher spending was due to the acquisition of tumblr which yahoo bought earlier this year for close to  billion and whose operating expenses are now counted on yahoo’s income statement according to cfo ken goldman but mayer has also been on a hiring binge at yahoo especially in engineering bringing  engineers aboard so far this year sales and marketing costs also rose climbing  on a yearoveryear basis while yahoo’s total operating costs in the quarter were held flat from a year ago at  billion they would have risen if the company hadn’t booked a restructuring charge in the yearearlier period mayer and cfo goldman both said during the company’s earnings conference call tuesday that expenses are expected to level off in  that may be just in time for yahoo shareholders since the company also issued a fourthquarter revenue forecast range that was slightly below wall street’s earlier expectations the new forecast signals that yahoo will post either little or no topline growth in  mayer’s first full year at the helm even though the company’s number of paid search clicks rose  in the third quarter the justcompleted quarter saw a huge decline in another important yahoo metric cash flow from operations net operating cash plunged  during the quarter compared with a year earlier and is down  for the first nine months of this year all this might be cause for alarm if not for yahoo’s lucrative stake in alibaba the biggest onlinecommerce company in china earnings wall discuss key earnings announcements before and after results come in learn more some wall street analysts estimate that at least half of yahoo’s  billion market valuation is owed to its alibaba shares which are expected to soar in value with an alibaba ipo sources have told this column that the offering will come next year and goldman said tuesday that yahoo does “expect that alibaba will ipo at some point” though he didn’t offer any time frame yahoo said it had amended a prior agreement with alibaba and will now sell at least  million shares of the company in any ipo down from at least  million shares previously yahoo invested  billion in alibaba in  in exchange for a  stake and still owns about a quarter of the company once it does sell alibaba shares yahoo will be able to book extraordinary gains from those transactions for at least several quarters as it did after selling a large alibaba stake last september yahoo has been using the gains from that sale to fund investments and buy back shares thereby reducing its share count and raising pershare earnings even as it does yahoo will continue to benefit from its equity interests in both alibaba and yahoo japan as it did in the third quarter yet the gains from any alibaba share sales will be booked in a limited number of quarters even as yahoo’s operations continue to struggle and investors just got a preview of what yahoo’s financials might look like after the alibaba gains are gone on a gaap basis yahoo’s net income plunged by  in the third quarter to  million or  cents per share that’s because last year’s thirdquarter earnings line ballooned by  billion with the sale of alibaba shares and  of net income for the third quarter was due to what’s called “earnings from equity interests” on yahoo’s income statement — which is primarily from the investments in yahoo japan and alibaba that line rose to  million in other words less than a quarter of yahoo’s net profit came from its own operations investors whose optimism has helped drive a doubling of yahoo’s share price since mayer took the ceo job in july  should be aware that they’re making a bet on a revenue turnaround that has yet to materialize unless yahoo’s investments begin to boost its top line growth investors should be nowhere near this stock once the company has booked most of the financial gains from its alibaba share sales note the author has no positions long or short in yahoo or any of its rivals more from marketwatch the reason jack bogle doesn’t fly first class says everything about his investing legacy stocks brace for volatility in earnings deluge fed meeting looms alphabet earnings a  billion hit for google potential youtube results for investors quote references goog   most popular oj simpson made over  while in prison and won’t have to give any of it to the goldman family the dark side of cruises this is what should really worry you about stocks stocks brace for volatility in earnings deluge fed meeting looms tour de france the tours first timers marketwatch partner center we want to hear from you join the conversation comment sponsored headlines advanced search stocks columns authors topics no results found   alphabet inc cl c us nasdaq goog    volumem open high low pe ratio div yield market capb john shinals tech investor  marketwatchcom topics bulletin investor alert topics john shinals tech investor twitter’s problems are the same as facebook’s  am feb    by john shinal now that a good bit of air has come out of twitter’s stockprice bubble the bears will be in charge of these shares for the nearterm writes john shinal apple ceo to wireless carriers let our people go  pm jan    by john shinal apple has to either win the smartphone and tablet war against android or roll out a new device that captures the next burst of growth in the mobile handheld market writes john shinal tesla putting out fires but stock is still overvalued  pm dec    by john shinal the back and forth this week between tesla motors and news outlets over 