e an attractive opportunity for investors company description founded in  by jerry yang and david filo yhoo is a global internet media company that offers communications content and a community platform that delivers consumer experiences and advertising solutions across digital screens revenues are derived between search  display  and other  the company has struggled in recent years with competition from google facebook and other social media platforms as indicated by revenue contraction in seven out of the past eight quarters ceo marissa mayer was hired in  to turnaround the failing core business but improvements have yet to materialize the significant rise in yhoo shares since her hiring are due to the companys holdings of alibaba group and yahoo japan corp otcpkyahoy spinoff details the spinoff of baba shares to yhoo shareholders is expected to occur in the q after yhoos lockup expires in september  the spinco will house all of yhoos remaining shares in baba and a legacy ancillary operating business of yahoo active trade or business or atb the spinco will assume no debt and yhoo will retain its cash the transaction still requires board irs and sec approval most importantly the company will look to the irs to provide a favorable ruling in regard to the taxfree nature of the deal the proposed transaction is similar in nature to the recent spinoff of liberty tripadvisor holdings inc nasdaqltrpa from liberty ventures nasdaqlvnta in  which we use as a proxy for timing purposes the proforma structure of yhoo and spinco is as follows opportunity   upside in  months the spinoff of ltrpa from lvnta took  days between announcement to completion and i believe this transaction should be no different the valuation framework deployed below contains a few assumptions that err on the side of conservatism given that the spinco will not be a pureplay the shares will trade at a discount to baba shares however given that the atb will likely be immaterial compared with the value of the baba shares  billion and relatively equal liquidity between the spinco shares and baba shares spinco will have  million baba shares vs the  million shares offered in the ipo i estimate that the discount will be minimal and likely in the neighborhood of  assuming this transaction goes forward shareholders can expect yahoy to be spunoff in a similar manner however given the potential taxable event i have assigned a  discount for the core yhoo business i am using the average analyst estimated ebitda for fy and applying a x evebitda multiple this multiple is significantly below comps and below analysts estimates who favor using a higher multiple closer to x by my estimates on a higher  ebitda level according to one analyst the peer group trades at x ebitda implying that i am using a  discount to peers i apply a  discount to yhoos net cash position as while i believe yahoos management will remain good stewards of capital the company has reduced gross shares outstanding by  since  for  billion there could be potential for dilutive spending by management the company has said that it anticipates returning  of the aftertax proceeds to shareholders so we know that at least half of the cash on hand will not be used inappropriately in addition to the individual component discounts i apply a  holdco discount to the remaining yahoy yhoo core business and yhoo net cash as i believe the street will ultimately assess a sumoftheparts discount on the holdco risks core yhoo continues decline revenue extac and adjusted ebitda were down  and  respectively in  and analysts are estimating that revenue and ebitda will fall  and  respectively in  according to bloomberg while mayer has tried to stabilize and grow the business there is no guarantee that she will be successful in the near future the valuation framework used considers this fact and if the core business turns around there is additional upside for shareholders unfavorable irs ruling while yhoo has enlisted the help of tax advisors before announcing the spinoff and even considering the ltrpa spinoff there is no guarantee that the irs will allow the taxfree deal if the irs does not give its approval shareholders are likely to value yhoo assuming baba and yahoy are fullytaxed which could push shares of yhoo down to   downside technical details in order to capture the spread described in the valuation section investors should short  shares of baba for every one share of yhoo and short  shares of yahoy for every one share of yhoo this refers to the shares traded in japan and not the adr that this article references these ratios will ensure yhoo shareholders are not impacted by the changes in baba and yahoy share prices borrowing costs are currently minimal conclusion while the arbitrage community may be somewhat apprehensive about taxrelated deals after the recent fallout from the shireabbvie cancelled merger the spinoff of baba shares from yhoo is far less likely to run into any trouble with the irs and the current upside makes this an attractive situation disclosure the author is long yhoo the author wrote this article themselves and it expresses their own opinions the author is not receiving compensation for it the author has no business relationship with any company whose stock is mentioned in this article additional disclosure i am long yhoo and short baba and jp in order to lock in the spread i may change or exit my position buy or sell shares without updating this article and without informing the seeking alpha community editors note this article discusses one or more securities that do not trade on a major us exchange please be aware of the risks associated with these stocksabout this articleexpandtagged investing ideas long ideas technology internet information providerswant to share your opinion on this article add a commentdisagree with this article submit your ownto report a factual error in this article click herefollow roundabout asset management and get email alerts access to th